SIMPLE: celluloid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Celluloid
<hw>Cel"lu*loid`</hw> <pr>(s⟦ecr⟧l"⟦usl⟧*loid)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cellul</ets>ose + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <def>A substance
composed essentially of gun cotton and camphor, and when pure resembling
ivory in texture and color, but variously colored to imitate coral,
tortoise shell, amber, malachite, etc. It is used in the manufacture of
jewelry and many small articles, as combs, brushes, collars, and cuffs;
-- originally called <altname>xylonite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cellulose</ent>⟦br⟧
